                          "snippet": "The TCPSocket class provides the ability to send a stream of data over TCP. TCPSockets maintain a stateful connection that starts with the connect member function. After successfully connecting to a server, you can use the send and recv member functions to send and receive data (similar to writing or reading from a file).",
