                          "title": "Byte Ordering Concept Little Endian Big Endian",
                          "url": "https://www.scribd.com/document/702198478/Byte-Ordering-Concept-Little-Endian-Big-Endian",
                          "snippet": "Big endian ordering stores the most significant byte at the lowest memory address, while little endian stores the least significant byte at the lowest address. Functions like htons() and htonl() are used to convert between host byte ordering and network byte ordering, which uses big endian.",
                          "publishedDate": 1756598400000,
                          "id": "2",
                          "domain": "scribd.com",
