                          "snippet": "architectures) is little endian. However, network byte order (aka big endian) is how bytes are ordered for use in \nvarious network protocols.",
                          "publishedDate": null,
                          "id": "6",
                          "domain": "brownson.net",
                          "maxVerbatimWordLimit": 30,
